Code base for Ember Kit from Lower East Kitchen

Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License
http://lowereastkitchen.com

Installation:
** Copy the Ember and PID_v1 folders to your Arduino libraries folder.
** Open the ember_arduino.pde file in the Arduino IDE.
** Load the file onto your chip.

Ways to load onto files your chip:

>>>Never use when plugged in!<<<

** FTDI cable from computer to header on Ember Kit.
** Remove ATMEGA328 and place in a programmer/Arduino socket.
** Break out pins from an Arduino to the Ember Kit board.  From BLK to GRN, the FTDI pins are:   RESET, RX, TX, 5V, GND, GND